description.0: The Conclusion to "The Brotherhood" Saga! Will James MacDonald be able to learn the origins of the phantom girl?
description.2: Manga Spidey returns and he's brought Manga Daredevil with him!
description.3: Magdalena's mother is unfairly targeted, while the young Russian girl undergoes change.
description.4: In the tradition of TALES TO ASTONISH, it's two classic characters in one cool comic! First, it's The Hulk by writer/artist Rob Haynes (DAREDEVIL: NINJA), then it's Thor by writer Marlan Harris and internationally-acclaimed artist Kia Asamiya!
description.5: Killraven reminisces on his childhood amidst Mint Juleps' attack. Having awakened, Mint Julep asks Killraven to join her on her mission to find out more about Martians' science and possibly lovers. Refusing her ultimatum, Killraven must now face the wrath of MINT JULEP!!
description.11: Collects Wolverine/Hulk (2002) #1-4.  Sam Keith (The Maxx, Zero Girl) returns to Marvel - and takes on two of Marvel's most popular - and toughest -- characters! A metal-clawed X-Man, an emerald behemoth and a scared little girl named Po what draws these three very different characters together? Answer: Expect the unexpected!
description.12: As Steve Rogers, he's a simple American just trying to clean up the neighborhood. As Captain America, he's a superhero who's in for the fight of his life against the man called Barricade!
description.13: Peter awakens in Africa where he battles Shathra with the help of some African allies! Back in the United States, MJ is leaving on a jet plane...to where?
description.15: Alex, Outlaw, and Taskmaster, claw their way through an army of mercenaries. Will the entire trio get out of this scrap alive? Plus, Alex agrees to take on Higashi as a client.
description.16: Bruce Banner and Sandra Verdugo are on the run from Agent Pratt! But when the agent finally tracks them down, Pratt may find that it's him that is on the run from Banner...and his big green friend!
description.18: Xorn has taken the special class into the woods for a lesson they won't soon forget. Meanwhile, Quentin Quire assembles his fellow revolutionaries and gives them a little kick, in the form of some Hypercortisone D! Here come the New X-Men!
description.20: Cap learns a terrible secret about S.H.I.E.L.D. as the terrorist master looks to end Captain America himself.
description.21: After being injured in a fire fight, the Punisher collapses and is taken in by his former neighbor, Joan. Together they must defend her peaceful cottage from the small army of Russian soldiers looking to finish what they started!
description.22: Who shot first?'Han'or'Greedo? Depending on which version of'Star Wars: A New Hope'you watch either answer is correct. Now, for the first time in Star Wars Tales #14, the question goes before a court of law! Han Solo is sued for the wrongful death of Greedo by the'Rodian's mother in "The Emperor's Court!"
description.23: Obi-Wan'and'Anakin'have their hands full protecting'Senator'Greyshade from attacks by'droid'assassins,'sky-bike'riding'Dug'assassins, and beautiful assassin princesses with diplomatic immunity. Meanwhile,'Autemand'Omin, the two'Senate Guards'who are also on the Greyshade assignment, discover a common link among the assassins, a link that strikes a little too close to home for Autem. Action and adventure during the time that the'Republic'ruled'the galaxy'and the'Jedi'were the glue that held the Republic together!
description.25: Gunz encounters something he has never seen on the job…a super villain with powers that rival no man.
description.28: Collects Daredevil (1998) #26-37.  The red-hot writer of ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN and ALIAS takes on Marvel's Man Without Fear! What will happen when Daredevil's greatest secret is exposed on the front page of New York City's tabloids? This collection features an entire year's worth of acclaimed DAREDEVIL issues (#26 - #37), plus tons of behind-the-scenes extras!
description.29: An all Ororo issue! From the pages of X-Treme X-Men, Storm roars into the spotlight with stories by the teams of Jason Pearson, J. Torres & Keron Grant and more!
description.30: SENTIENT Part one! Franklin Richards creates an artificial being out of data.  How will the new creature interact with the FF?
description.31: THE TRIAL OF THE CENTURY PART 1 Power Man and Iron Fist approach Matt Murdock to defend White Tiger on a libelous murder charge. Will Daredevil's defense hold up in a court of law?
description.34: Can Aurora and Wild Child survive a trap set by the preying Sabretooth? The Director has a plan for the menacing mutant -Weapon Zero!
description.35: Hawk-Owl has adopted a son to carry out his legacy. And his name is Hank. However, things don't turn out to be quite that easy...
description.37: James MacDonald's life has been changed forever, all because of a mysterious little girl who prophesizes tragic events that actually occur.
description.39: Manga Spidey returns following the smash-hit success of his original one-shot! And this time he's swinging in with a collective of Marvel's street-level heroes!
description.40: The ground shakes when Geo debuts -- and kicks Soldier X's butt!
description.41: WAR OF THE WORLDS! Killraven saves a young boy named John from a Martian attack after they took his mother's life right before his eyes. Reminiscing on how his mother was killed, Killraven decides to protect John from any harm caused by anyone. But the martians aren't the only ones Killraven and his gang have to watch out for when Mint Julep and her army storm in. Will Killraven be able to save the freemen and still be able to protect John?
description.44: The cosmic balance is thrown off. What is the new order of the universe in Paradise X?
description.45: Spidey receives help from Buddhist deity, Tara!
description.47: Grizzly and Rhino have had enough! Together, they decide once and for all that it's time to give up the villain life, and play it straight for a while! The only problem: they keep annoying the hell out of each other!
description.48: There's a new Black Panther in town, and his name is Kevin Cole! His first task - a trial by fire, taking on the 66 Bridges gang who have been wreaking havoc on New York City!
description.49: May Parker has had it with her double life and quit her career as the sensational Spider-Girl. But can she be persuaded to return to web-slinging?
description.50: With Venus free from her contract and Vivisector and Phat's relationship in the open, the team is back and better than ever! Their first mission- save the Orphan from Arnie Lunt!
description.52: Not likely to be employee of the month anytime soon, Wolverine drops a bomb on the mob - who happens to be his new employer!
description.56: Collects Cable (1993) #101-107.  The one-man-army known as Cable heads to the world's hotspots to spread peace - and he's not afraid to back his message up with bullets!
description.57: Collects Spider-Man: Quality of Life #1-4.  Spider-Man squares off against the lethal Lizard in this spectacular tale.
description.58: Life is hard for Captain Marvel right now, but not nearly as bad as when he was dying of cancer. Genis embraces the heart of a warrior.
description.63: Just when Alex thought his life had lost all meaning and control, he is saved by Arcade. But does Arcade have ulterior motives when he offers to rebuild Alex's theme park?
description.70: Dagobah'is a mysterious place. Beneath the heavy canopy of ancient trees lies a strange jungle inhabited by creatures in caves and swamps not seen elsewhere. Dagobah is also home to the greatest living'Jedi Master,'Yoda. It's here that he has trained young'Leia Skywalker'to take her rightful place in the'Jedi Order. Though she has quickly learned what he's taught her, she is not a'Jedi'yet. She has two important final tasks to complete. Yoda, too, has a final mission. His home is about to become a battleground, as he faces the fiercest soldier the'dark side'has ever commanded:'Darth Vader!'
description.71: Sandra is alive after all - and Bruce might not be the murderer he thought he was. He just needs to stay alive and awake long enough to escape Agent Pratt and his team at Home Base!
description.73: At the scene of a grisly murder, Cyclops and Beast discover an inhaler containing the drug Hypercortisone D, a mutant steroid. Who's pushing these drugs to young mutants? What will this mean for students back at the mansion?
description.74: Spidey crashes the interview where Shathra is spreading rumors about him! Can Peter keep his Spider-Man reputation intact?
description.78: To combat a plant-devouring virus, and a monarch who has power to back up dreams of domination, these new heroes and some old friends will have to give their all.  Alliances are forged, dreams are shattered, and lives are put on the line in the name of freedom.
description.81: The Punisher comes face to face with terrorism in Northern Ireland.
description.85: Frankie's brother has a strange obsession with his wife…or maybe Frankie’s wife has a strange obsession with her brother-in-law?
description.87: Two Vultures don't make a right! After the original Vulture gets a set of wings, Spidey has to contend with two birdbrains at the same time! To make matter's worse, he may just be coming down with something...
description.90: Doctor Strange visits a melancholy Peter Parker in a dream to warn him of a danger that he has brought back with him from the Astral Plane!
description.91: Collects Avengers (1998) #41-55, Avengers Annual 2001.  The warlord known as Kang the Conqueror returns - and this time he's enslaving the entire Earth!
description.94: Collects Peter Parker: Spider-Man (1999) #44-47.The Green Goblin is back, and Norman Osborn won't stop until he has the wall-crawler's heart on a silver platter. He's looking to hurt Spider-Man through his heart by putting everyone Peter cares for in danger!
description.95: Collects Spider-Man's Tangled Web (2001) #13-17.  An impressive list of indie creators take hard looks at living in the not-so-friendly neighborhood of the world-famous web-slinger! This is the perfect book for those who never thought they'd ever read -- and enjoy -- a Spider-Man story!
description.96: Collects Deadline (2002) #1-4.  What's it really like to be a reporter the Daily Bugle? Find out in an urban noir thriller illustrated by Guy Davis (The Marquis)! What's it like to write about Marvel's larger-than-life superhumans... especially if you think they're a bunch of immature brats? Rookie reporter Katherine Farrell hates "The Capes." They wear ridiculous costumes. They have petty feuds. They run around destroying public property when real heroes like cops and firemen are sacrificing their lives to help others. But, hey, Kat's a newbie, so it's the beat she's stuck with. That is, unless she can nail a big story and move up to the City Crime Desk next to her hero Ben Urich. Trouble is, her career, not to mention her life, is threatoned when she uncovers the identity of a super-villian serial killer!
description.97: Liberty's Doom concludes here! And only the Mangaverse's Avengers can quell Doom's wrath!
description.98: Still mourning the comatose state of Flash Thompson, Spidey also has to face a strange woman, and old crimes commited by a corporation.

1.text: Jennifer and a mysterious woman are willing to sacrifice their lives to save the world from a bio-toxin that would infect millions.

6.text: Like a mythic knight of legend, Iron Man battles an honest to goodness fire-breathing dragon.

7.text: Locke may have his doubts about Elektra, but now he’s committed to her reformation! Under the tutelage of a new master, will the assassin become a defender instead of a killer?

8.text: Gigi has been hiding the truth about the bombing from Chamber. Once Chamber figures it out, he rushes back to the ESU campus to find Amber held at gunpoint!

9.text: An anime adventure of sci-fi action in the widescreen MarvelScope format! On a faraway planet, a simple girl from a small corner of the galaxy finds herself in sole possession of the secrets of the universe! Follow her thrill-packed quest to discover the truth in this five-issue series plotted & illustrated by Steve Uy!

10.text: Posing as the gaijin Kiyoshi, Logan befriends a beautiful geisha named Mariko.

14.text: Guest-starring the Vulture and Spider-Man! Following their attack on Timby, Al swears revenge on the Rothstein brothers and exacts justice.

17.text: PUBLIC SCRUTINY PART 2 Someone posing as Spider-Man has gone a crime-spree all across Manhattan. Will Spidey be able to clear his name with the police or will he be dodging bullets for the rest of his career?

18.text: Xorn has taken the special class into the woods for a lesson they won't soon forget. Meanwhile, Quentin Quire assembles his fellow revolutionaries and gives them a little kick, in the form of some Hypercortisone D! Here come the New X-Men!

Xorn has taken the special class into the woods for a lesson they won't soon forget. Meanwhile, Quentin Quire assembles his fellow revolutionaries and gives them a little kick, in the form of some Hypercortisone D! Here come the New X-Men!

19.text: When Citizen V and V-Battalion find themselves in danger, they call upon the New Thunderbolts for a rescue!

24.text: HELLFIRE AND BRIMSTONE PART 3 Wolverine and Cyclops head to the Savage Land on a mission for the U.S. government!

25.text: Gunz encounters something he has never seen on the job…a super villain with powers that rival no man.

27.text: PUBLIC SCRUTINY PART 1 Witness the debut of Ultimate Rhino as the mechanized menace tears through the streets of Manhattan!

32.text: Mojo kidnaps Nocturne and Morph to be part of his world's nonstop reality shows. Guest-starring Longshot!

33.text: Yellowjacket and the Wasp, trapped in extradimensional torment! To rescue them, the Avengers must appeal to a cosmic entity's good side...literally!

36.text: Thor stands before the United Nations to declare his intentions and expose the corrupt officials who intend to stop him!

38.text: Jennifer Montez warns James MacDonald that a phantom girl has told her James will die if he attempts to put out the fire on a very specific building…

42.text: Iron Man is trapped back in time in a realm of might and magic. Now, Tony Stark is a fugitive in a strange new world that relies more on magic than science.

43.text: Jeremy Locke finds it difficult to ‘sleep tight’…especially when trapped in his bedroom by the deadly Elektra! The trail of blood has led to this- a psychotic face off for the truth. Will Elektra be able to make the kill shot? Or will her own personal crisis lead her down a path less familiar?

46.text: Anti-mutant sentiment runs high as Kitty and Karma are accosted by the FBI, while fellow mutant Shola Inkosi is attacked by a riotous mob.

53.text: The festive mood that the X-Men are enjoying is shattered after Kitty Pryde's mood takes a turn. What's on her mind? And how will it affect the team going forward?

54.text: On Counter-Earth, the Thunderbolts must battle Anomaly.

55.text: Investigating the murder of a teenage girl, Cage suddenly learns that a three-way gang war is under way for control of the turf he calls home. And what better way to disrupt the stalemate than offering his services to the highest bidder?

56.text: Macedonians plan to "cleanse" their Albanian ethnic rivals from their shared country. Enter Cable, a freedom fighter with no allegiances and a powerful philosophy of peace, and who's not afraid to back it up with cold bullets.

57.text: When a corrupt corporation blocks Dr. Curt Conners' bid to help cure his cancer-stricken wife, his only hope for curing Martha might involve unleashing the monster within' the Lizard

59.text: Chamber and Amber investigate the bombing on the ESU campus. Gigi points them to the group Magnetic North and Chamber fights one of their members in a club!

60.text: Wolverine…in Feudal Japan! Logan enters a battle midway, where he must claw and cut a swath through an army of militant samurai!

61.text: The lush, fully-painted miniseries concludes! Takashi and Lyle Crawford make their next move while Elektra lies in wait. Ghosts of dead Hand ninjas are summoned forth to take down Marvel’s mightiest assassin! And when the dust settles…the Beast awakes.

62.text: S.H.I.E.L.D. wants Blackheath’s body. The Thunderbolts must comply or risk their freedom by resisting.

64.text: A contract on Matt Murdock's life is somehow connected to the Kingpin's apparent murder at the hands of the mysterious Mr. Silke and the crime lord's own underbosses.

65.text: Half of New York's criminals are gunning for Spider-Man's head and to make matters worse, the web-slinger must now contend with the re-emergence of the Green Goblin.

66.text: A team of Avengers from disparate timelines fights to safeguard the future from Immortus, the Lord of Time.

67.text: The X-Men follow the trail of Rogue's nightmares to a hidden corner of the globe where the great dinosaurs of the Jurassic and Cretaceous Ages continue to rule.

68.text: Adored by humans, reviled by their fellow mutants, X-Force does the dirty jobs that others can't, or won't. All they want in return is fame, money, sex, power and lucrative endorsement deals.

69.text: Kraven and Timby are still without a script (and still crashing at Scott Baio’s house!), but that’s the least of their problems. The Rothsteins’ are back with their hired goons, and they’re set on making Al’s life a living hell!

72.text: LEGACY PART 6 The electrifying conclusion to LEGACY. To saved his loved ones, Spidey must take down the Goblin once and for all!

73.text: At the scene of a grisly murder, Cyclops and Beast discover an inhaler containing the drug Hypercortisone D, a mutant steroid. Who's pushing these drugs to young mutants? What will this mean for students back at the mansion?

75.text: On Counter-Earth, Mach-3 is forced to make a difficult decision.

76.text: This deluxe, hardcover volume collects the first year's stories from Incredible Hulk Vol. 1: Return of the Monster, Incredible Hulk Vol. 2: Boiling Point and Startling Stories: Banner' plus other behind-the-scenes bonus material.

77.text: Manga's most popular creators re-imagine Marvel's most popular characters. The result: all-new, all-different excitement with big eyes, big hands and lots of tech.

78.text: To combat a plant-devouring virus, and a monarch who has power to back up dreams of domination, these new heroes and some old friends will have to give their all.  Alliances are forged, dreams are shattered, and lives are put on the line in the name of freedom.

79.text: The X-Men embark on their first-ever field trip trying to follow Professor Xavier's dream to spread peace. But, while traveling the world on his author tour, Professor Xavier's greatest secret is exposed. And they soon learn that human hostility towards mutants is not limited to American soil.

80.text: Darth Vader has landed on a distant world to track down a mysterious Jedi. But, instead of a Jedi Knight, he is confronted by a cadre of bounty hunters who have come to the conclusion that ganging up on, and defeating, the Sith Lord will bring them fame and fortune. Boy, are they in for a wake-up call! Meanwhile, on Coruscant, the ranks of those plotting to kill Emperor Palpatine are thinned as the co-conspirators begin targeting each other.

83.text: HELLFIRE AND BRIMSTONE PART 2 The Brotherhood of Mutants begins a nuclear disarmament campaign in the Middle East. Back in America, tempers flare as Cyclops' and Wolverine's rivalry comes to a head!

84.text: In a reality in which the Lizard has turned half of the United States into reptiles, Curt Connors decides to take drastic measures to right his wrongs. Will the Exiles be able to protect both human and reptilian?

85.text: Frankie's brother has a strange obsession with his wife…or maybe Frankie’s wife has a strange obsession with her brother-in-law?

87.text: Two Vultures don't make a right! After the original Vulture gets a set of wings, Spidey has to contend with two birdbrains at the same time! To make matter's worse, he may just be coming down with something...

Two Vultures don't make a right! After the original Vulture gets a set of wings, Spidey has to contend with two birdbrains at the same time! To make matter's worse, he may just be coming down with something...

88.text: LEGACY PART 5 With Osborn's newfound ability to turn into the Goblin with a simple injection of Oz, Spider-Man finds himself facing his most powerful enemy ever!

89.text: HOMELAND SECURITY PART 2 Hawkeye and Black Widow go hunting for aliens in New York City!

91.text: When duty calls, the legendary Avengers answer' but Kang is a foe unlike any other; his ultimate goal is nothing short of global domination, to impose his will over all.

92.text: This romantic period piece defied industry expectations. At long last, all is revealed about the incredible forces that molded Wolverine, the world's most perfect killing machine with a heart as big as the great outdoors.

93.text: Bruce Banner is found hiding in plain sight at a roadside convenience store' caught abruptly between a gun-wielding madman, a constricting circle of local police and dark, predatory forces.

94.text: The Green Goblin is back, and Norman Osborn won't stop until he has the wall-crawler's heart on a silver platter.  He's looking to hurt Spider-Man through his heart' putting everyone Peter cares for in danger.

95.text: Illustrated by Duncan Fegredo, Sean Phillips & Giuseppe Camuncoli

96.text: Rookie reporter Katherine Farrell is stuck with the super-hero beat unless she can nail a big story and move up to the City Crime Desk. Trouble is, her career' and her life' are threatened when she uncovers the identity of a super-villain serial killer.

99.text: After a physics experiment goes horribly wrong, it's up to Kitty, Karma, and the Genoshan mutant Shola Inkosi to rescue the staff and students.
